The members of the Welsh National Assembly fear that they will be called muppets
Among some of the members of the National Assembly, there was confusion, which is the result of a proposal to change their title to Members of the Welsh Parliament (MWP).
The idea was based on plans to transform the assembly into a Welsh Parliament.
The members of the assembly from all sides of the political scene are concerned that they may be mocked.
One Labour MP expressed concerns about his group, saying that the new name rhymes with the Welsh words "twp" and "pwp".
For readers outside Wales: in Welsh, the word "twp" means stupid, and the word "pwp" means excrement.
A politician from the Plaid Cymru party stated that his group was “dissatisfied” with the proposal and presented other solutions.
A member of the Welsh Conservative Party said that his party was "open" to a change of name, but he pointed out that the word "MWP" was very similar to the word "muppet".
In this case, the Welsh letter "w" is pronounced similar to the letter "u" in the English Yorkshire dialect.
The assembly committee, which is currently working on a draft law amending the name, took the following position: "Naturally, the final decision on the future title of the members of the assembly will be theirs".
The 2017 Government of Wales Act gave the Welsh National Assembly the right to change its name.
In June, the committee published the results of the public consultation on the proposal, and the conversion of the Assembly to the Welsh Parliament gained broad support.
In addition, the committee supported the proposal to change the title of the members of the assembly to the “Member of the Welsh Parliament”, that is, the WMP in English, although the abbreviation “MWP” was the most popular among the public.
The difficulties in reaching consensus are a nuisance for Elin Jones, the chairman of the assembly, who should present a bill in the coming weeks.
The law introducing reforms will also take into account other changes in the way the assembly works, including the rules on recalling members and the structure of the comitology system.
Members of the National Assembly will be able to vote on their future title when discussing the bill.
