Supporters of the change of name, including Prime Minister Zoran Zaew, claim that it is worth paying the price for the possibility of joining Macedonia – one of the countries created after the collapse of Yugoslavia – to organisations such as the European Union or NATO.
"I voted in favour of the future of my country so that young people in Macedonia can live free under the umbrella of the European Union. EU membership will provide us all with greater security," said 79-year-old Oliwiera Georgijewska from Skopje.
