In front of the parliament building in Skopje, 54-year-old Vladimir Kawardarkov prepared a small scene and placed chairs in front of tents spread by boycotts of the referendum.
"We support membership of NATO and the EU, but we want to join these organisations with their head up, not their back door," Kawardarkov said.
“We are a poor country, but we have our dignity.
