Prime Minister Zaew claims that NATO membership will bring the necessary investments in Macedonia, with an unemployment rate of more than 20%.
"I believe that a huge majority will support a change of name in a referendum, because 80% of citizens support the European Union and NATO," Zaew said after voting.
