Morales' relentless rhetoric deprived Chileans of any remnants of goodwill, suggested.
Bolivia and Chile will resume their talks at some point, but this will be very difficult in the face of the situation.
In the case of both countries, there has been no exchange of ambassadors since 1962.
Eduardo Rodríguez Veltzé, former president and representative of Bolivia in the Hague, disagreed that the decision-making process of the court was extremely rapid.
Monday will bring Bolivia "a unique opportunity to start a new era in relations with Chile" and the opportunity to "end a 139-year period of disputes with mutual benefit", he said.
Calzadilla also denied that Morales — still one of Latin’s most popular presidents — was using the subject of sea access as part of the political game.
