Almanac: inventor of the Geiger counter
And now the page from our release "Sunday Morning" Almanac: September 30, 1882, 136 years ago... the day that future physicist Johannes Wilhelm "Hans" Geiger was born in Germany.
Geiger developed a method to detect and measure radioactivity, which eventually led to the creation of a device known as the Geiger counter.
Since then, the Geiger counter has become both an element of science and pop culture, as in the 1950 film "Bells of Coronado", in which these seemingly unlikely cowboy scientists Roy Rogers and Dale Evans performed:
